<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1675,1868]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1717,1743]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body vermiform; female genitalia appressed to coxae; scapular tubercles and setae present, prodorsal shield without frontal lobe; legs with usual segmentation and setae, empodium entire.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1675,1868]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This genus consists of 25 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[646,892,1801,1827]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[751,808,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
